<2ND_LINE>PM-Box Office,0480</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`Biloxi Blues' At Top Of Box Office List</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RICHARD DE ATLEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Biloxi Blues'' shot into first place in the
weekend box office movie-rankings the first week of its public
release, displacing ``Police Academy 5: Assignment Miami Beach.''
   The Neil Simon film starring Matthew Broderick, who gets his
Army basic training in the Deep South, earned more than $7 million
in its debut week.
   In second place was another new movie, ``Johnny Be Good,''
starring Anthony Michael Hall as a high school star quarterback
sought by unscrupulous college recruiters. The movie sold tickets
worth $5.2 million.
   A re-release of the Disney cartoon movie ``The Fox And The
Hound'' earned $4.8 million for third place. The movie about
juvenile innocence between two natural enemies was first released
in 1981.
   ``Police Academy 5: Assignment Miami Beach'' slipped to fourth
place, earning $3.6 million.
   Academy Award nominee Robin Williams' ``Good Morning, Vietnam,''
was in fifth place with $3.3 million, followed by another
Disney-Touchstone film, ``D.O.A.,'' which earned $2.51 million for
sixth place in its second week of release.
   Alan Alda's ``A New Life,'' about the misadventures of marriage,
divorce and romance, earned more than $2.5 million in its debut
week for seventh place.
   The movie was written and directed by Alda and stars him along
with Ann-Margret, Hal Linden, Veronica Hamel, John Shea and Mary
Kay Place.
   ``Masquerade'' was in eighth place with $2 million, followed by
``Vice Versa'' with $1.8 million and ``Moonstruck'' in tenth place
with $1.7 million.
   Here are the top films for the weekend as tallied by Exhibitor
Relations Co., with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater
screens, average per screen, total gross, number of weeks in
release, and estimated production costs when available.
   1. ``Biloxi Blues,'' Universal, $7.09 million, 1,239 screens,
$5,725 per screen, $7.09 million, one week, n-a.
   2. ``Johnny Be Good,'' Orion, $5.2 million, 1,168 screens,
$4,494 per screen, $5.2 million, one week, n-a.
   3. ``The Fox And The Hound,'' Disney, $4.8 million, 1,567
screens, $3,075 per screen, one week, $4.8 million.
   4. ``Police Academy 5: Assignment Miami Beach,'' Warner Bros.,
$3.6 million, 1,700 screens, $2,170 per screen, $11.1 million, two
weeks, n-a.
   5. ``Good Morning, Vietnam,'' Disney-Touchstone, $3.3 million,
1,486 screens, $2,236 per screen, $101.1 million, 13 weeks, $21
million.
   6. ``D.O.A.'' Disney-Touchstone, $2.51 million, 908 screens,
$2,774 per screen, $7.5 million, two weeks, n-a.
   7. ``A New Life,'' Paramount, $2.50 million, 796 screens, $3,147
per screen, $2.50 million, one week, n-a.
   8. ``Masquerade,'' MGM-UA, $2.0 million, 1,002 screens, $2,003
per screen, $10.6 million, three weeks, n-a.
   9. ``Vice Versa,'' Columbia, $1.8 million, 1,219 screens, $1,485
per screen, $10.5 million, three weeks, n-a.
   10. ``Moonstruck,'' MGM-UA, $1.7 million, 1,041 screens, $1,679
per screen, $55.1 million, 14 weeks.
</TEXT>
