<2ND_LINE>PM-Israel-Text,0233</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>With PM-Israel, Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Text of Closure Announcement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the text of the Israeli government
announcement Monday ordering the closure of the occupied West Bank
and Gaza Strip for three days. It was released in English by the
government:
   In order to maintain law, order and security in Judea, Samaria
(West Bank) and Gaza the following measures will be taken by order
of the security forces:
   1. Starting Tuesday at 0100 (6 p.m. EST Monday) (Arab) residents
of Judea and Samaria will not be able to enter or exit Israel's
borders for three days.
   2. A curfew will be imposed on the Gaza region starting this
evening (Monday) at 2200 hours (3 p.m. EST) and will be lifted on
April 1 at 0300 (8 p.m. EST Thursday).
   3. Residents of Judea, Samaria and Gaza will not be allowed to
leave the territories via the Jordan River bridges. The bridges
will remain open for entry.
   4. Starting tonight (Monday) Judea, Samaria and Gaza will be
declared a closed military region.
   5. Media personnel will be allowed to enter the territories and
travel within them only upon authorization of the Israeli Defense
Forces spokesman's office.
   Journalists authorized to enter the areas will be able to do so
only if accompanied by an IDF representative.
   Signed: IDF spokesman Brig. Gen. Ephraim Lapid.
</TEXT>
