<HEAD>Village Fire Kills Six Children In Bangladesh</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire in a northern village destroyed
more than 150 mud-and-straw homes and killed at least six children.
   The fire on Monday left 1,000 people homeless in Jangaldi
village, 60 miles north of Dhaka, the independent Bengali-language
daily Ittefaq said.
   It said the six children killed were trapped inside homes during
the two-hour fire, which was put out by villagers using buckets of
water.
</TEXT>
