<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Italy-Mafia,0092</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>18 Suspects Arrested In Construction Contract Probe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eighteen people were arrested in an
investigation into attempts by the Mafia to scare off competition
for construction contracts.
   The charges against the suspects, who were arrested Monday,
included criminal association, extortion and illegal use of
explosives.
   Police said the probe began six months ago after a series of
dynamite attacks on companies that won contracts to build part of
the Palermo-Messina highway and a new section of track for the rail
line linking the two cities.
</TEXT>
