<HEAD>6 Killed, 1 Hurt In Avalanche</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout to UPDATE with 6 dead, 1 injured. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six people were killed and one was
injured when a group of young West German skiers and their guide
were buried by an avalanche in the Jam Valley of Tyrol province,
authorities said.
   The accident happened Monday morning, but authorities did not
become aware of it until late in the afternoon because all
electricity and telephone lines to the area had been interrupted by
another avalanche, a police spokesman from the area told Austrian
television.
   The spokesman said the six people dug out of the snow were
already dead and a seventh was injured. No names of the skiers
involved were released.
