<HEAD>Friday Named to Head Weather Service</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Elbert W. Friday, deputy director of the
National Weather Service, has been named head of that agency, the
National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration announced today.
   Friday succeeds Richard D. Hallgren, who has been named
executive director of the American Meteorological Society.
   The National Weather Service is the federal agency that collects
weather information and issues forecasts and warnings.
