<HEAD>Asian Ambassadors To Hold Meetings on Regional Issues</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   American ambassadors to East Asian and Pacific
nations will meet in Hong Kong on April 8-10 for an annual
discussion of policy and administrative affairs, the State
Department announced Tuesday.
   Gaston Sigur, the assistant secretary for East Asian and Pacific
affairs, will chair the session. Beforehand he will travel to Seoul
on April 2-5 and Tokyo on April 5-7 for discussions with Korean and
Japanese officials.
   Sigur will meet Soviet Vice Foreign Minister Igor Rogachev in
Paris on April 25-26. It will be the fourth U.S.-Soviet meeting on
Asian problems, notably the continuing Vietnamese occupation of
Cambodia, since 1985 when President Reagan and Soviet leader
Mikhail S. Gorbachev agreed to periodic conferences on troubled
regions.
</TEXT>
