<DOCNO> AP880329-0141 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-03-29-88 1429EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Korea-Award     03-29 0092</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Korea-Award,0095</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Former AP Photographer Wins Award in South Korea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A retired Associated Press
photographer has won a lifetime achievement award for his 37 years
covering the country, it was announced Tuesday.
   The Seoul Journalists Club said it would present its award to
Kim Chon-kil, 58, on April 8 at the Korean Press Center.
   Kim retired from the news service in January after 37 years with
the AP's Seoul Bureau. During that time, he covered the Korean War,
South Korea's turbulent politics and many other assignments.
