<HEAD>President Names Rader For US Claims Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan plans to nominate Randall M.
Rader, an aide to Sen. Orrin G. Hatch, R-Utah, as a judge of the
U.S. Claims Court, the White House announced Tuesday.
   If confirmed by the Senate, Rader will succeed Robert M. Seto.
   Since 1987, Rader has been chief counsel and staff director for
the minority side of the Senate Judiciary subcommittee on patents,
copyrights and trademarks and counsel to Hatch.
