<HEAD>Journalists Cry Foul Over Treatment In Panama</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Overseas Press Club sent a letter to Gen.
Manuel Antonio Noriega on Tuesday protesting what it described as
``harsh treatment'' of foreign journalists in Panama City.
   The organization of journalists said in a letter addressed to
the defense forces commander in Panama that the arrests of eight
journalists in Panama on Monday violated United Nations rules on
human rights.
   The journalists were arrested along with 20 opposition leaders
when troops raided the Marriott Hotel, which serves as the
headquarters of Panama's opposition and the foreign press. The
journalists were released Tuesday.
