off legal challenges in the Iran-Contra case, prompting a rebuke
from Utah's attorney general.
   ``It was a little bizarre that an independent counsel would be
seeking help from the state attorneys general,'' said David
Wilkinson, who holds that office in Utah.
   But spokesmen for other attorneys general said they saw nothing
unusual with the March 15 letter that Walsh's associate, Jeffrey
Toobin, sent to the U.S. attorneys and attorneys general in 50
states. The letter seeks information about other cases involving
immunity.
