<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street 10am,0233</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks prices staged a broad-based rally in
early trading today following Monday's mixed performance.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 12.77 to 1,992.54
in the first half hour of trading on Wall Street.
   Advancing issues outpaced declines by about 4 to 1 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 864 up, 220 down, and 406 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board was about 24.21 million shares.
   Traders attributed the improvement to several factors, including
the dollar's stability in foreign exchange, which lessened fears of
inflatin and higher interest rates, and some bargain hunting.
   ``The market is in an oversold condition,'' explained Larry
Wachtel, market strategist and first vice president at
Prudential-Bache Securities Inc. ``You usually snap back from that.
It could be nothing more or nothing less than that.''
   The NYSE composite index was up 0.97 at 147.08. At the American
Stock Exchange, the market value index rose 0.92 to 292.92.
   On Monday, the Dow Jones industrial average closed a scant 0.82
higher at 1,979.77, after posting moderate declines through much of
the trading session.
   Declining issues outpaced advances by more than 2-to-1 on the
NYSE, with 1,059 issues falling, 468 gaining and 420 unchanged. Big
Board volume totaled 142.82 million shares, down from 163.17
million in Friday's session.
