<HEAD>Spiegel to Acquire Honeybee</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAK BROOK, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Spiegel Inc., the mail-order retailer,
has announced an agreement to acquire Honeybee Inc., a specialty
retailer of women's apparel for $23 million.
   The definitive merger agreement call for Spiegel to buy about 75
percent of Honeybee stock from members of the controlling Einbender
family for $7.60 a share and to buy the rest of the stock from
public shareholders for $11.18 a share.
   New York-based Honeybee closed at $10.25 a share Monday on the
American Stock Exchange, up $2.37{ from Friday's close.
   Honeybee sells higher-priced brand name and designer women's
clothing through catalogs and 18 retail stores in New York, New
Jersey, Pennsylvania, Illinois, Missouri, Connecticut and
Tennessee. It had sales of about $33 million for the year ended
Jan. 2.
   Oak Brook-based Spiegel sells apparel, household furnishings and
other general merchandise through catalogs distributed to more than
30 million U.S. households.
