<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Japan-Autos     03-29 0161</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Japan-Autos,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Japan's February Motor Vehicle Exports Drop 0.3 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Japanese exports of cars, trucks and buses fell 0.3
percent last month from February 1987 levels, the Japan Automobile
Manufacturer's Association announced Tuesday.
   Japan's automakers exported 528,605 vehicles last month, the
association said.
   The decline followed a 9.1 percent slide in January and
December's 2 percent climb, the first in 11 months.
   ``The environment surrounding Japan's automobile exports
continues to be severe,'' a JAMA official said. ``Shipments to some
markets showed growth, but those increases are marginal since they
are small markets.''
   Exports to the country's two largest markets, the United States
and the European Community, remained stalled as the yen continued
to climb.
   Shipments to the United States totaled 208,266 vehicles in
February, down 8.2 percent from a year earlier, while those to
Europe slid 5.4 percent to 133,473 vehicles.
   The strong yen has eroded the price-competitiveness of
Japanese-made autos, as well as those produced overseas.
</TEXT>
