<HEAD>New Business to Bring 135 Jobs to Mexico, Mo.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A New Hampshire company Monday said it would
build a catalog sales distribution center in Mexico, bringing 135
new jobs to the east-central Missouri city.
   Brookstone Co. of Peterborough, N.H. is building a
100,000-square-foot facility on a 16.9-acre site. Investment in the
plant was expected to be near $9.5 million.
   The city was told last week that it had been awarded a $500,000
grant to extend streets, water lines and sewer lines to the site.
   Construction was to be completed by July to allow the plant to
begin distribution of products purchased for the Christmas season.
   ``Brookstone's commitment represents a significant step in the
growth of the Mexico-area economy,'' said Mexico Mayor Larry Webber.
   Brookstone officials said they selected Mexico because of the
available work force and the positive relationship city officials
have with existing employers.
   Brookstone offers tools, household items and automotive
products. Besides it's catalog sales operation, Brookstone has 80
retail outlets in 26 states.
