<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Volcker-MBIA     03-29 0156</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Volcker-MBIA,0164</2ND_LINE>
<BYLINE>Volcker Elected to MBIA Board</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WHITE PLAINS, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Federal Reserve Board chairman
Paul Volcker and David Elliott, president of MBIA Corp., were
elected directors of MBIA Inc., the company said Tuesday.
   Volcker will also serve as a consultant to the company, it was
announced by William O. Bailey, chairman and chief executive
officer of MBIA.
   MBIA Inc. is the holding company of Muncipal Bonds Investors
Assurance Corp., a leading insurer of municipal bonds.
   Volcker is chairman of James Wolfensohn Inc., a New York
investment banking firm, and was chairman of the Federal Reserve
Board from 1979 to August 1987.
   Elliott has been the president and chief operating officer of
MBIA Corp. since its formation in late 1986.
   MBIA Corp. insures municipal bonds, including new issues and
bonds traded in the secondary market.
</TEXT>
